**`analyticsApi.ts` — WebSocket + subscription Map without guaranteed cleanup**

The `taskSubscriptions` map accumulates callbacks. If a subscriber never calls the returned cleanup function, the entry lives for the lifetime of the `AnalyticsAPI` instance.

```ts
// CURRENT — leak if caller drops the unsubscribe reference
subscribeToTask(taskId: string, callback: (task: AnalysisTask) => void): () => void {
  this.taskSubscriptions.set(taskId, callback);
  // ...
  return () => this.taskSubscriptions.delete(taskId);
}
```

```ts
// FIX — add a WeakRef-based or TTL-based eviction, plus a destroy() method
destroy(): void {
  this.taskSubscriptions.clear();
  this.websocket?.close();
  this.websocket = null;
}
```

**`exportApi.ts` — DOM node appended but only removed on success path**

```ts
// CURRENT — if link.click() throws, the <a> leaks into the DOM
document.body.appendChild(link);
link.click();
document.body.removeChild(link);   // never reached on exception
```

```ts
// FIX — use try/finally
document.body.appendChild(link);
try {
  link.click();
} finally {
  document.body.removeChild(link);
}
```

**`analyticsApi.ts` — `reconnectAttempts` not reset on clean close**

If the WebSocket closes cleanly after a prior failed reconnect, `reconnectAttempts` stays elevated and the next failure window is shorter than intended.

```ts
// ADD — reset in the onopen handler
ws.onopen = () => {
  this.reconnectAttempts = 0;   // ← add this line
  // existing subscription re-send logic
};
```

---

**`agent-memory.test.ts` — `typeMap` objects allocated on every function call**

```ts
// CURRENT — two reverse-lookup maps rebuilt on each call
function memoryToJsonLd(memory: Memory) {
  const typeMap = { episodic: 'EpisodicMemory', ... };  // new object every call
}
function jsonLdToMemory(jsonLd) {
  const typeMap = { EpisodicMemory: 'episodic', ... };  // new object every call
}
```

```ts
// FIX — module-level constants
const MEMORY_TYPE_TO_JSONLD: Record<Memory['type'], string> = {
  episodic: 'EpisodicMemory',
  semantic: 'SemanticMemory',
  procedural: 'ProceduralMemory',
  session: 'SessionMemory',
};
const JSONLD_TO_MEMORY_TYPE = Object.fromEntries(
  Object.entries(MEMORY_TYPE_TO_JSONLD).map(([k, v]) => [v, k])
) as Record<string, Memory['type']>;
```

**`constraintsApi.ts` — `getConstraintTypeName` rebuilds array every call**

```ts
// CURRENT
export const getConstraintTypeName = (type: number): string => {
  const names = ['None', 'Separation', 'Boundary', 'Alignment', 'Cluster'];  // new array
  return names[type] || 'Unknown';
};
```

```ts
// FIX
const CONSTRAINT_TYPE_NAMES = ['None', 'Separation', 'Boundary', 'Alignment', 'Cluster'] as const;
export const getConstraintTypeName = (type: number): string =>
  CONSTRAINT_TYPE_NAMES[type] ?? 'Unknown';
```

**`schemaMappings.ts` — `deepMergeVisual` called with empty fallback objects**

When the server returns no visual data, `v.glow || {}` passes a fresh `{}` into `deepMergeVisual`, which then iterates the entire defaults object to copy it — wasted work.

```ts
// CURRENT — always merges even when server provides nothing
glow: deepMergeVisual(DEFAULT_GLOW_SETTINGS, v.glow || {}),
```

```ts
// FIX — short-circuit when stored is empty
glow: v.glow && Object.keys(v.glow).length > 0
  ? deepMergeVisual(DEFAULT_GLOW_SETTINGS, v.glow)
  : { ...DEFAULT_GLOW_SETTINGS },
```

**`workspaceApi.ts` — `searchParams.toString()` called twice**

```ts
// CURRENT
const url = `/list${searchParams.toString() ? `?${searchParams}` : ''}`;
```

```ts
// FIX
const qs = searchParams.toString();
const url = qs ? `/list?${qs}` : '/list';
```

